---
import SiteNav from "./SiteNav.astro";
---

<header class="hero">
  <SiteNav />

  <div class="hero-grid">
    <div class="hero-copy">
      <div class="hero-badges">
        <span class="hero-badge">Reusable resources</span>
        <span class="hero-badge">Customizable packs</span>
        <span class="hero-badge">CLI + API + MCP</span>
      </div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Link reusable analysis resources without losing flexibility</p>
      <h1 class="hero-title">Turn scripts, tools, and notebooks into reusable work.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Data scientists constantly adapt CLI tools, scripts, packages, and notebooks to the current
        dataset or project. Linkar helps you keep that work reusable at the same time: package each
        step as a template, connect steps through bindings, and run everything through a short CLI
        or a machine-readable local API.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="button button-primary" href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}tutorials/getting-started/`}>Start Here</a>
        <a class="button button-secondary" href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}explanations/why-linkar/`}>Why Linkar</a>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-metrics">
        <div class="metric-card">
          <strong>Templates stay standalone</strong>
          <span>Each template declares its inputs and outputs and should be testable on its own.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="metric-card">
          <strong>Bindings remove repeated wiring</strong>
          <span>Reusable connection logic maps outputs to inputs so you do not keep re-entering the same choices.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="hero-panel">
      <div class="terminal-window">
        <div class="terminal-bar">
          <span></span><span></span><span></span>
        </div>
        <pre><code>$ linkar project init --name study
cd study

$ linkar pack add ~/github/izkf_genomics_pack --id izkf
$ linkar run cellranger_atac --fastqs ./fastqs
$ linkar run atac_qc
$ linkar inspect run atac_qc_001

study/
  atac_qc/
  .linkar/
    runs/
      atac_qc_001/
        results/
        .linkar/
          meta.json
          runtime.json</code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>
